{
  "text": "FAU-type zeolite with a particle size of 10 − 20nm was prepared according to the procedure described in detail elsewhere ( [CITATION_1] ). Hydrophilic FAU-type zeolites were used for water molecule detection. The zeolite X with FAU type framework structure (FAUX) was synthesized from a clear precursor suspension with a molar composition: 9 Na 2 O: 1.1 Al 2 O 3 : 10 SiO 2 : 45 H 2 O. The clear precursor suspension was stabilized via control mixing of two solutions, i.e., silica-and aluminabased dissolved in NaOH and H 2 O. The final precursor suspension was aged for 24h at room temperature, and then subjected to hydrothermal crystallization at 50 o C for 45h. The solid products (nanosized FAU-X zeolite) were recovered by centrifugation (25000rpm for 4h), purified with H 2 O until pH= 7 and then freezedried. The FAU-X zeolite nanocrystals can absorb up to 32% water, as revealed by thermogravimetry. The high hydrophilicity of the FAU-X crystals is due to the high aluminum content (Si/Al = 1).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "32965482"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "32965482": {
      "title": "Template-free nanosized faujasite-type zeolites",
      "abstract": "Nanosized faujasite crystals are promising catalysts and adsorbents. The template-free synthesis of such zeolites with a narrow particle size distribution and excellent thermal stability that lead to superior catalytic performances is now reported."
    }
  }
}